istic size of $0.52-0.69~R_{\\star}$\nfor the larger, long lived features. This is close to the values of\n$0.51-0.53~R_{\\star}$ derived from 3D RHD models of stellar surfaces. We\nconclude that interferometric imaging of this star is in line with predictions\nof 3D RHD models but that short-term imaging is needed to more stringently test\npredictions of convection in RSGs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 29 Jun 2021 18:00:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-10-13"}
